git init : initialise with github repository

git config --global user.name/user.email : configuration of user's infos in terminal environment

git clone https://[user's_token]github.com/[user_name]/[repository_name]:clone repository from github to terminal environment

git add . : declare files which we want to push to original repository

git commit : make files ready to push or commit -m [commit message]
 
git push : push all added files to to original repository in github

git pull : retrieve github old version repository modified by another collaborator before pushing the new update  

git branch [new branch]: create new branch / git branch -b [new branch] : to create a branch and switch to it at the same time

git status : view all selected files and their changes

git log : display all recent updates and user that
 
